2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description:
Overview

DECIMATION Tie-In!

House of M has forever changed the Xavier Institute and as if the kids didn’t have enough to worry about, assassin X-23 comes to the school! Trouble is brewing as one of the X-Men’s deadliest villains, William Stryker, is making news again and this time, God is on HIS side! Part 2 (of 4)!
2005-01-01|2005-12-30.name: Childhood's End Part 2

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description: Power Man & Iron Fist vs. Cable & Deadpool! Totally `Nuff Said! (We know Power Man is known as Cage now, but it sounds better to say it the old way when you have the ampersand in there!) Plus, the BAD Girls mess up the thief who stole the Dominus Objective computer drive! And what the heck is the Dominus Objective anyway? Part 2 (of 4).
2005-01-01|2005-12-30.name: Bosom Buddies, Part 2 of 4: Friendly Fire

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description:
CROSSOVER PART 1 Reed Richards has found a way to travel to an alternate Earth in another dimension. Being the imaginauts they are, the Fantastic Four set out on a mission of ultimate discovery -but discover the Marvel Zombies.

Overview

"Crossover," part 1 of 3. Ultimate Starts Month begins here! Mark Millar returns to Ultimate Fantastic Four, and he's brought X-Men: Phoenix Endsong superstar Greg Land with him! Even in their short careers, the Ultimate FF have seen a lot of amazing things ­ but nothing will prepare them for the world they're about to enter! Reed Richards has used his scientific genius to contact an Earth in a surprisingly familiar parallel dimension ­ and he's ready to visit.
2005-01-01|2005-12-30.name: Crossover: Part 1

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description: Professor Chang blasts Beast Boy with his new G.A.R.T.H. Gun and transforms him into...Garthzilla! When the giant green monster starts trashing the city, the Titans have no choice but to bust out their secret weapon...the Titans Go-Bot 5!
2005-01-01|2005-12-30.name: Garsaurus REX!

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description:
Overview
The award-winning team of Busiek and Nord continue their adaptation of one of Robert E. Howard's greatest Conan stories, with the second part of "The Tower of the Elephant." Conan, at the side of Taurus, Prince of Thieves, assaults the dreaded Elephant Tower-but deadly peril awaits at every turn, from hungry lions to giant spiders, and it'll take all his barbarian skill merely to stay alive long enough to make it inside. Yet, once inside, the tower holds secrets far stranger and darker than anything Conan could have prepared for.
2005-01-01|2005-12-30.name: The Tower and the Elephant: The Prince of Thieves

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description:
Stand-alone issue! Susan and Reed Richards are among comicdom’s happiest, most stable couples. So why, then, does Reed perpetually forget their anniversary?

When it happens yet again, it’s up to Sue’s best girlfriends — Alicia, Crystal, and the Sensational She-Hulk — to cheer her up with a night out on the town… Marvel style! While dishing about their former crushes, Sue reveals an untold episode from her past involving… the Black Panther?!
2005-01-01|2005-12-30.name: Desperate Housewife

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description: "THE OTHER: EVOLVE OR DIE" PART 8 (OF 12) THE SPIDER-MAN CROSSOVER EVENT OF THE DECADE CONTINUES HERE! Beaten to the edge of death, hovering in a place short of heaven or hell, Spidey is about to embark on a journey unlike anything he's ever experienced. If he's going to have any hope to thwart Morlun's obscene mission, then he's got two choices: Evolve or die...
2005-01-01|2005-12-30.name: The Other - Evolve Or Die, Part 8 of 12: Aftermath

2005-01-01|2005-12-30.description:
Though he once killed in the name of the nascent Meiji government, even an infamous manslayer such as "Hitokiri Battôsai" might grow weary and vow never to kill again. As a new age dawns, there are those who yet cling to the ways of bloodshed, and see the days of peace and prosperity Kenshin and others like him fought so hard to bring forth as betrayal. In ten days' time, the enemies of Kenshin will come for him, and all who stand beside him are in danger. Is the time of earthly justice truly at hand?
